Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editAddTrimMetal(25.10)                                editAddTrimMetal(25.10)

Name
       editAddTrimMetal - Adds trim metal at the specified location

Syntax
       editAddTrimMetal

       [-help]

       [-layer <string>]

       -location {<x y>}

       [-mask <integer>]

       [-snap_to_end]

       Adds trim metal at the specified location.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editAddTrimMetal parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editAddTrimMetal

       -layer <string>
              Specifies  the layer on which the trim metal is to be added. The
              layer name should be a routing layer defined in  the  LEF  file.
              Note  that you can specify only one valid layer name. That is, a
              layer name list is not supported. If the -layer  option  is  not
              specified,   editAddTrimMetal adds the trim metal on the nearest
              object.

              Check the Examples section below to see how to use this option.

       -location {<x y>}
              Specifies the coordinates for  the  center  point  of  the  trim
              metal. The tool may adjust automatically to the closest location
              that is best for the trim metal.

       -mask <integer>
              Specifies  the  mask  value  for  the  trim  metal.  However, if
              USEMETALMASK is already defined for the trim layer in  the  tech
              LEF, you cannot define the mask value here.

       -snap_to_end
              Specifies  that  the trim metal should be snapped to the closest
              end of the selected pin or wire.

Examples
       In the following illustration, the pin Y has two pin shapes, one on  M1
       and the other on M3. The Pin Y on Inst A is selected.

              * If you add trim metal with the -layer option (as specified be-
                low),  the  tool will add the trim metal on the pin shape that
                is on layer M1.

                editAddTrimMetal -layer M1 -location {50 37}

              * If you add trim metal without the -layer option (as  shown  in
                the  command  below),  the tool will add the trim metal on the
                nearest pin, which in this case is on M3.

                editAddTrimMetal -location {50 37}

